<font color="#FF0000">IMPACT ON FAMILY RELATIONSHIPS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Dec 12 14:21:28 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Although I was not alive during the war, I have lived through it my whole life.  My father is a Vietnam Vet and I have been able to observe first hand the effects the war had on him.  Instead of the fun loving father that my mother married, he has been the protector afraid to let his guard down.  This past year I have seen glimpses of the person my father was before Vietnam.  It's refreshing.  I love my father and pray he will find peace.  I just wish we wouldn't have lost this many years to a cause that died long ago. 
<p><code>-- heatherh@chc64.com  (Heather) </code><p>


